                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-108-victim1066 t18220911-108-viclabel588"></join>. On the 2d of September the prisoner came and called for a glass of beer, the knives and forks were in the parlour cupboard, he was alone in the room.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-108-person1068">
                  ABEL 
                  GARNHAM
               <interp inst="t18220911-108-person1068" type="surname" value="GARNHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-108-person1068" type="given" value="ABEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-108-person1068" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the passage of the public-house, and watched the prisoner - I saw him rummaging in the closet, and saw a handkerchief containing knives and forks on a chair. I knocked at the glass, and asked what he was doing; he folded them up and put them in his pocket. I went in and stopped him, he claimed the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-108-person1069">
